{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"975be537-42b0-426c-87e3-8a91f472e84f","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively speaks Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is **no longer needed**. You can simply remove it.\n\nYour `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required — it makes MSTest use the MTP runner. Only the bridge property is redundant now.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MZxWsZiwt3SRFf2aFWD3BS","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0173Eh9TFnJK4U1yS7skSvn2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-402d19642e264042bed75d38197a6016/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-402d19642e264042bed75d38197a6016/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"d58cd4b9-21fb-42fd-9d73-579a92df1f72","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true. They want to know about native MTP support in .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). The key change is:\n\n1. .NET 10 SDK's `dotnet test` uses MTP natively — the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed.\n2. In fact, in .NET 10, `dotnet test` defaults to using MTP when the test project is an MTP-based project (i.e., has `EnableMSTestRunner`/`TestingPlatformCaptureOutput` etc.).\n\n\n3. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 SDK to opt into the MTP-based `dotnet test` experience, but in .NET 10 this is now the default behavior.\n\nSo they should remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from their project file since it's no longer necessary, while keeping `EnableMSTestRunner` to maintain the MTP-based executable test project setup.","outputTokens":662,"requestId":"5C29:28D076:AFEA3:DE5CE:69F54B84"},"id":"13d76590-b7f9-4550-a80d-933f0be1561f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:55:44.130Z","parentId":"95cebdae-1903-4a67-a23d-7725f7c8a4b4"}
